imdb.title: Ultraman
imdb.plot: Shinjiro Hayata learns that his father passed on the "Ultraman Factor" to him and fights against evil.

episodes.title: The Man from NY
episodes.plot: While meeting with Rena, Shinjiro suddenly gets a call to stop a rampaging alien; journalist Kotaro Higashi witnesses the whole incident.

episodes.title: Flames of Fury
episodes.plot: Kotaro tries to find out more about the strange "maids" he saw just before the mass disappearance in Tokyo, and Moroboshi talks to Agent Adad.

episodes.title: The Man without the Light
episodes.plot: Alien Pedant appears, makes his demands and gives humankind 24 hours to respond; Taro attempts to convince Jack to let him help.

episodes.title: Attack on SSSP
episodes.plot: While Jack, Taro and Seven close in on their target, SSSP headquarters comes under attack; Maya makes a difficult decision.

episodes.title: The Golden Fortress
episodes.plot: With time running out, Shinjiro joins Jack, Seven and Taro to face the Golden Fortress, the ultimate weapon unleashed by Pedant.

episodes.title: ULTRAMAN No.6
episodes.plot: Jack and Taro try to destroy the Golden Fortress from within; in the battle that follows, Shin and Shinjiro confront Pedant together.

episodes.title: A Power That Shouldn't Be On This Earth
episodes.plot: Decades since he last merged with Ultraman, Shin Hayata learns of a new threat to Earth. His son, Shinjiro, also shows signs of superhuman strength.

episodes.title: An Inescapable Fate
episodes.plot: Wearing a protosuit, Shin is critically injured while saving Shinjiro from Bemular's attack. In desperation, Shinjiro returns to rescue his father.

episodes.title: Being Ultraman Isn't Bad
episodes.plot: With Bemular paving the way for other alien species to attack Earth, SSSP's Edo asks Shinjiro to take on the mantle of Ultraman.

episodes.title: Release the Limiter!
episodes.plot: Shinjiro is sent on a mission to exterminate a hostile alien, but the target flees into the city, endangering countless civilians.

episodes.title: City of Aliens
episodes.plot: After uncovering evidence of alien involvement in a string of bizarre homicides, SSSP agent Moroboshi contacts an informant inside an alien enclave.

episodes.title: The Curse of Ultraman
episodes.plot: Shinjiro's reluctance to execute homicidal aliens deeply concerns agent Moroboshi. Shin shares with his son what it truly means to be Ultraman.

episodes.title: Hidden Thoughts
episodes.plot: Embattled at first, Shinjiro finds his resolve and activates a latent power during his fight against a hostile alien. Rena prepares for a big concert.

episodes.title: The Beginning of Truth
episodes.plot: At Rena's concert, an alien calling himself Adad demands a confrontation with Ultraman. Things go from bad to worse when Bemular joins the fray.

episodes.title: Nice To Meet You, Brother
episodes.plot: Shinijiro fears that his cover may be blown by an underclassman. Later on, he's taken aback when a rogue Ultraman shows up to aid him in battle.

episodes.title: Star Council
episodes.plot: Seiji dreams of a day when aliens are accepted openly on Earth. Hoping to fight for this cause, he pleads with the SSSP to bring him on board.

episodes.title: You As You Are
episodes.plot: Seiji has a tense confrontation with Shinjiro and Moroboshi over the use of his powers. Rena asks Shinjiro to give Ultraman a message.

episodes.title: Ace Killer
episodes.plot: Moroboshi, Shinjiro and the might of the SSSP sets out to protect Seiji on his quest to punish those responsible for the airline tragedy 12 years ago.

episodes.title: A Real Ultraman
episodes.plot: The Ultraman trio are fighting a losing battle against the mercenaries, but just when things seem hopeless, Shinjiro's dormant power finally awakens.
